    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-14T16:21:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-14T16:21:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">357.AD/8–1453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d744fn1">This telegram was drafted and cleared by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRD1">Murphy</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-14T17:21:00-04:00"
                            >August 14, 1953—5:21 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Eyes only for <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName>.… Swedish
                    information interesting but does not help us much in developing position
                    regarding political conference. Even though time is short I feel you should ask
                        <persName corresp="#p_HDHAC1">Hammarskjold</persName> whether Swedish
                    representative Peking might not inform <persName corresp="#p_CEL1">Chou
                        En-lai</persName> in strictest confidence US preference for demilitarized
                    zone Korea or mutually acceptable alternative suitable Asian site for political
                    conference and that we propose be guided by provisions Article 60 Armistice
                    Agreement in respect composition and agenda.<note n="2" xml:id="d744fn2"
                        >According to telegram <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 587 from
                            <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>, Aug. 17, 1953, <persName
                            corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> made this proposal to <persName
                            corresp="#p_HDHAC1">Hammarskjold</persName> who said he would do it.
                        (357.AD/8–1753)</note>
                </p>
                <p>This may elicit some tentative indication regarding Chinese thinking which might
                    be helpful.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
